BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:xGe5eSPrAKSLgNKiMObug
SUMMARY:Rainbow Elder Breakfast
DTSTAMP:20260326T230625Z
DTSTART:20260404T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description We cherish our LGBTQ\\+ elders and believe that mag
	ical and meaningful connections can happen at any age. These breakfasts gi
	ve folks 50\\+ a chance to connect with each other\, eat good food and enj
	oy a morning boost of community that the Eastside has been long overdue fo
	r. Pride Across the Bridge is partnering with the marvelous Sno-Valley Sen
	ior Center to create this space. We meet on the first Saturday of each mon
	th at different locations on the Eastside from 10:30am-12pm. This is a fre
	e to attend event with food and drink available for purchase\, but not req
	uired! If you would like assistance with paying for a bill\, please let ou
	r facilitator know. Financial barriers should not be the hurdle to you enj
	oyably connecting with your community. Contact us for any questions or to 
	RSVP: Info@PrideAcrossTheBridge.org or \\(971\\) 380-5873 Guidelines: This
	 is a safe space for all. Any behavior that goes against the 2SLGBTQIA\\+ 
	and BIPOC community will result in an individual being asked to leave. Fee
	l free to bring friends/family if they will make you more comfortable. Car
	egivers are welcome to join in! Confidentiality Policy: PAB is dedicated t
	o creating a safe and inclusive space for our 2SLGBTQIA\\+ elders. All sha
	red information within the group\, including gender identity\, sexual orie
	ntation\, and personal experiences\, must remain confidential and not be d
	isclosed without explicit consent. Members have the right to anonymity\, a
	nd no one should feel pressured to reveal personal details. By participati
	ng\, members agree to adhere to this policy. April 4th 2026 - Carnation Ca
	fe: 4760 Tolt Ave\, Carnation\, WA\, United States\, Washington Local Tran
	sit: Bus: Snoqualmie Valley Transportation\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com
	/events/#/details/rainbow-elder-breakfast/18425342/2026-04-04T00\n\nFrom S
	EAtoday - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/rainbow-elder-breakfast/1
	8425342/2026-04-04T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
